{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36861380", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36861380/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36861380/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/tag/v1.2.2", "id": 36861380, "author": {"login": "lmb", "id": 368392, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM2ODM5Mg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/368392?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb", "html_url": "https://github.com/lmb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTM2ODYxMzgw", "tag_name": "v1.2.2", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Fix passing arguments to child processes", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2021-01-25T14:23:27Z", "published_at": "2021-01-25T14:26:38Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/tarball/v1.2.2", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/zipball/v1.2.2", "body": "The previous release introduces a bug when starting a child process: the argument vector (aka argv) is populated incorrectly. The result is that processes that use argv will likely fail and processes that don't use argv will fail to upgrade."}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36846364", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36846364/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/36846364/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/cloudflare/tableflip/releases/tag/v1.2.1", "id": 36846364, "author": {"login": "lmb", "id": 368392, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM2ODM5Mg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/368392?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb", "html_url": "https://github.com/lmb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lmb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTM2ODQ2MzY0", "tag_name": "v1.2.1", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Fix clearing O_NONBLOCK on upgrade", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2021-01-22T18:28:28Z", "published_at": "2021-01-25T09:25:31Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/tarball/v1.2.1", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/tableflip/zipball/v1.2.1", "body": "The Go runtime has annoying behaviour around setting and clearing\r\nO_NONBLOCK: exec.Cmd.Start() ends up calling os.File.Fd() for any\r\nfile in exec.Cmd.ExtraFiles. os.File.Fd() disables both the use\r\nof the runtime poller for the file and clears O_NONBLOCK from\r\nthe underlying open file descriptor.\r\n\r\nThis can lead to goroutines hanging in a parent process, after at least\r\none failed upgrade. The bug manifests by goroutines  which rely on\r\neither a deadline or interruption via Close() to be unblocked being stuck\r\nin read or accept like syscalls,. As far as I can tell we've not experienced\r\nthis problem in production, so it's most likely quite rare."}
